<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n03012c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03012c">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03012c"> 12(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> round tower to / protect clerics</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[<mark>round towers</mark>, a distinctive feature of native Irish architecture]</font> were used as belfries, and as places where the inhabitants of a monastery might retire with their most treasured possessions in case of a sudden attack &hellip; <font color="green">[its]</font> great height, and its small doorway, generally about fourteen feet from the ground, enabled <mark><font color="green">[the monks]</font> to resist the attacks</mark> of an enemy chiefly armed with bows and arrows. <small> J.M. Flood, <a name="JMFI" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JMFI"><cite title="source">Ireland: Its Saints and Scholars</cite></a> (n.d) 117f</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
